{
  "texts": [
    "Using AlexNet and GoogleNet architectures, they reported a classification accuracy of 100% for both networks.",
    "Ahsan et al.",
    "34 discusses the use of deep learning algorithms to automatically classify diabetic foot ulcers (DFU), a serious complication of diabetes that can lead to lower limb amputation if untreated.",
    "The authors examined various convolutional neural network (CNN) architectures, including AlexNet, VGG16, VGG19, GoogleNet, ResNet50, MobileNet, SqueezeNet, and DenseNet.",
    "They used these models to categorize infection and ischemia in the DFU2020 dataset."
  ]
}